<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-03T19:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-03T19:36:00-05:00" n="1124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1124">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/1217</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Representative <persName type="from">Rodgers</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-03T18:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>114. In reply to Department’s 116 June 5, [2] 5 p.m. Fee as stated
                            prescribed;, declared necessary for supervision in order to protect
                            public. This action indicated in my mail despatch No. 57.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rodgers</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>